<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
If you are citing a work which has no author, the first few words of the title should be used. 
The title of a journal is italicised. Quotation marks are used around the title of an article.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&#34;Study smarter&#34; (2056) outlined the benefits of&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: &hellip;according to a recent study (&#34;Study smarter&#34;, 2056).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&#34;Study smarter&#34; (2056) observed that &#34;students are able to improve their 
	performance by&hellip;&#34; (p. 11).
	<br>
	Alternatively: &#34;Students are able to improve their performance by&hellip;&#34; 
	(&#34;Study smarter&#34;, 2056, p. 11).
</blockquote>
